reviewText: The instructo's pronounciation is always not clear. And the subtitles are misleading.

This course was highly informative, the structure was easy to follow and I felt that the breadth was sufficient. II really appreciated the examples when they were given but would have liked more case studies and further diversification of the content types. The readings were good and the instructor was clear, but I often found myself bored with the format of a lecture-and-reading-styled learning and zoning out as a result. The best parts of the course were the initial reading, the TED talk and the video on the Growth Share matrix.

Dear Prof Ralf Wilden,Thank you for sharing interesting concepts such as value proposition, the concept of ambidexterity,the idea of "Blue Ocean Strategy" is also an idea to be reckon, as we often read about it. Also on the exploration and exploitation ideas in the TED talk video by Mr Knut Haanaes.  Thank you once again for sharing a systematic MOOC.
